recordings.loc: San Simon, Cochise County, Arizona
recordings.rmk:
This is an immature male which has been seen in the canyon for a handfull of days drawing large crowds to see it.  It was photographed at 10 am in a completely different canyon 11 miles car travel (maybe less for the direct flight).  The bird is reported as being fairly vocal as I got to witness.  It was near dusk and the bird flew in quite vocal to it's seemingly popular roost.  I was a good 150 feet away from the bird that was across the canyon in mid canopy level.  Habitat is riparian canyon with sycamores in pine oak woodland canyon setting.

The audio was not altered.

recordings.file-name: XC567160-Final Recordings_Eared Quetzal- Portal, AZ, John Hands Picnic Area -1.mp3
recordings.rmk: Bird was calling from high in pines at  approximately 50-70ft  up. It moved around a roughly 200 foot radius throughout the time observed and eventually settled into a roost site as it got dark. The bird roosted  on a bare branch 2 feet from the trunk of a pine for the evening. It continued to vocalize off and on even after it settled on to the roost branch. Vocalizations ceased just after sunset.
